        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=PHP is prone to multiple vulnerabilities.|insight=The following flaws exist:

  - Improper validation of TIFF start data in 'exif_process_TIFF_in_JPEG' function in
  'ext/exif/exif.c' script.

  - Improper validation of IFD sizes in 'exif_process_TIFF_in_JPEG' function in 'ext/exif/exif.c'
  script.

  - Improper construction of spprintf arguments, in 'exif_process_TIFF_in_JPEG' function in
  'ext/exif/exif.c' script.

  - Error in 'grapheme_strpos function' in 'ext/intl/grapheme/grapheme_string.c'.

  - Error in 'xml_parse_into_struct' function in 'ext/xml/xml.c' script.

  - The 'bcpowmod' function in 'ext/bcmath/bcmath.c' improperly modifies certain data structures.

  - Improper validation of input passed to 'bcpowmod' function in 'ext/bcmath/bcmath.c' script.

  - Error in 'grapheme_strpos' function in ext/intl/grapheme/grapheme_string.c script.|affected=PHP prior to version 5.5.35, 5.6.x prior to 5.6.21 and 7.x
  prior to 7.0.6 on Linux.|impact=Successfully exploiting these issues allow remote attackers to
  cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read) or possibly have unspecified other impact.|solution=Update to version 5.5.35, 5.6.21, 7.0.6 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
