        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=PHP is prone to a use-after-free vulnerability in a used
  third-pary library.|insight=The flaw exists due to a use-after-free in onig_new_deluxe()
  in regext.c of the third-party library Oniguruma 6.9.2 which is used by PHP.

  The attacker provides a pair of a regex pattern and a string, with a multi-byte encoding that gets
  handled by onig_new_deluxe().|affected=PHP version before 7.1.32 and 7.3.x before 7.3.9.|impact=This flaw allows attackers to potentially cause information
  disclosure, denial of service, or possibly code execution by providing a crafted regular
  expression.|solution=Update to version 7.1.32, 7.3.9 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
