      <host>127.0.0.1<asset asset_id="f8f9e241-3239-45db-b797-db1b0320e24b" /><hostname>host1.example.com</hostname></host>
      <port>445/tcp</port>
      <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.108294">
        <type>nvt</type>
        <name>Samba Server 'CVE-2017-14746' Use-after-free Vulnerability</name>
        <family>General</family>
        <cvss_base>9.8</cvss_base>
        <severities score="9.8">
          <severity type="cvss_base_v3">
            <origin>NVD</origin>
            <date>2022-08-16T13:01:00Z</date>
            <score>9.8</score>
            <value>CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H</value>
          </severity>
        </severities>
        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=Samba is prone to a use-after-free vulnerability.|insight=The flaw exists due to a client which may use an SMB1
  request to manipulate the contents of heap space.|affected=Samba versions 4.0.0 to 4.5.14, 4.6.x prior to 4.6.11, 4.7.x
  prior to 4.7.3 with enabled SMBv1 support.|impact=A malicious SMB1 request can be used to control the contents
  of heap memory via a deallocated heap pointer. It is possible this may be used to compromise
  the SMB server.|solution=Update to Samba 4.5.15, 4.6.11, 4.7.3 or later.  Workaround:

  Prevent SMB1 access to the server by setting the parameter:

  server min protocol = SMB2

  to the [global] section of your smb.conf and restart smbd. This prevents a SMB1 access to the
  server. Note this could cause older clients to be unable to connect to the server.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to Samba 4.5.15, 4.6.11, 4.7.3 or later.  Workaround:

  Prevent SMB1 access to the server by setting the parameter:

  server min protocol = SMB2

  to the [global] section of your smb.conf and restart smbd. This prevents a SMB1 access to the
  server. Note this could cause older clients to be unable to connect to the server.</solution>
        <refs>
