        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=The OpenSSH client code between 5.4 and 7.1p1 contains experimental support for resuming SSH-connections (roaming).
  The matching server code has never been shipped, but the client code was enabled by default and could be tricked by a malicious
  server into leaking client memory to the server, including private client user keys. The authentication of the server host key prevents exploitation
  by a man-in-the-middle, so this information leak is restricted to connections to malicious or compromised servers.|insight=|affected=OpenSSH &gt;= 5.4 &lt; 7.1p2|impact=|solution=Update to 7.1p2 or newer.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
