        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=Samba is prone to a MITM authentication validation bypass vulnerability.|insight=The flaw is due to error in function
  '_krb5_extract_ticket' where the KDC-REP service name must be obtained from
  encrypted version stored in 'enc_part' instead of the unencrypted version
  stored in 'ticket'. Use of the unencrypted version provides an opportunity
  for successful server impersonation and other attacks.|affected=All versions of Samba from 4.0.0 before
  4.6.6 or 4.5.12 or 4.4.15.

  Note: All versions of Samba from 4.0.0 onwards using embedded Heimdal Kerberos.
  Samba binaries built against MIT Kerberos are not vulnerable.|impact=Successfully exploiting this issue will allow
  a MITM attacker to impersonate a trusted server and thus gain elevated access
  to the domain by returning malicious replication or authorization data.|solution=Upgrade to Samba 4.6.6 or 4.5.12 or 4.4.15
  or later or apply the patch from below.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Upgrade to Samba 4.6.6 or 4.5.12 or 4.4.15
  or later or apply the patch from below.</solution>
