        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=Drupal is prone to a remote code execution (RCE) vulnerability.|insight=The Drupal project uses the PEAR Archive_Tar library. The PEAR Archive_Tar
  library has released a security update that impacts Drupal. Multiple vulnerabilities are possible if Drupal is
  configured to allow .tar, .tar.gz, .bz2, or .tlz file uploads and processes them.|affected=Drupal 7.x, 8.8.x and prior, 8.9.x and 9.0.x.|impact=|solution=Update to version 7.75, 8.8.12, 8.9.10, 9.0.9 or later. To mitigate this
  issue, prevent untrusted users from uploading .tar, .tar.gz, .bz2, or .tlz files.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 7.75, 8.8.12, 8.9.10, 9.0.9 or later. To mitigate this
  issue, prevent untrusted users from uploading .tar, .tar.gz, .bz2, or .tlz files.</solution>
