        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N|summary=Apache HTTP Server is prone to a vulnerability in mod_session_crypto.|insight=mod_sessioncrypto is encrypting its data/cookie using the
  configured ciphers with possibly either CBC or ECB modes of operation (AES256-CBC by default),
  hence no selectable or builtin authenticated encryption. This makes it vulnerable to padding
  oracle attacks, particularly with CBC. An authentication tag (SipHash MAC) is now added to
  prevent such attacks.|affected=Apache HTTP Server version 2.4.1 through 2.4.23.|impact=|solution=Update to version 2.4.25 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
