  DNS packets (which can be supplied as UDP requests) can be abused to consume excessive amounts of CPU
  on the Samba AD DC (only). (CVE-2020-10745)

  - The AD DC NBT server in Samba 4.0 will enter a CPU spin and not process further requests once it
  receives an empty (zero-length) UDP packet to port 137. (CVE-2020-14303)|affected=All Samba versions since 4.0.0.|impact=|solution=Update to version 4.10.17, 4.11.11, 4.12.4 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
