      <host>127.0.0.1<asset asset_id="f8f9e241-3239-45db-b797-db1b0320e24b" /><hostname>host1.example.com</hostname></host>
      <port>80/tcp</port>
      <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.803737">
        <type>nvt</type>
        <name>PHP &lt; 5.5.2 Session Fixation Vulnerability (Aug 2013)</name>
        <family>Web application abuses</family>
        <cvss_base>6.8</cvss_base>
        <severities score="6.8">
          <severity type="cvss_base_v2">
            <origin />
            <date>2013-08-19T06:33:50Z</date>
            <score>6.8</score>
            <value>AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:P</value>
          </severity>
        </severities>
        <tags>cvss_base_vector=AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:P|summary=PHP is prone to a session fixation vulnerability.|insight=Session fixation vulnerability in the Sessions subsystem in
  PHP allows remote attackers to hijack web sessions by specifying a session ID.|affected=PHP versions prior to 5.5.2 if an application is using the
  Sessions subsystem of PHP.|impact=|solution=- Update to PHP version 5.5.2 or later and set
  'session.use_strict_mode' in php.ini to 'On'

  - make adoptive session with user land code as described in the referenced PHP strict_sessions
  document|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">- Update to PHP version 5.5.2 or later and set
  'session.use_strict_mode' in php.ini to 'On'

  - make adoptive session with user land code as described in the referenced PHP strict_sessions
  document</solution>
        <refs>
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2011-4718" />
          <ref type="url" id="https://wiki.php.net/rfc/strict_sessions" />
          <ref type="url" id="https://wiki.php.net/rfc/strict_sessions#current_solution" />
