      <host>127.0.0.1<asset asset_id="f8f9e241-3239-45db-b797-db1b0320e24b" /><hostname>host1.example.com</hostname></host>
      <port>22/tcp</port>
      <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.118572">
        <type>nvt</type>
        <name>OpenBSD OpenSSH &lt; 9.6 Multiple Vulnerabilities (Terrapin Attack)</name>
        <family>General</family>
        <cvss_base>6.5</cvss_base>
        <severities score="6.5">
          <severity type="cvss_base_v3">
            <origin>NVD</origin>
            <date>2024-01-03T19:40:00Z</date>
            <score>6.5</score>
            <value>CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:N</value>
          </severity>
        </severities>
        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:N|summary=OpenBSD OpenSSH is prone to multiple vulnerabilities.|insight=The following vulnerabilities exist:

  - CVE-2023-48795: The SSH transport protocol with certain OpenSSH extensions allows remote
  attackers to bypass integrity checks such that some packets are omitted (from the extension
  negotiation message), and a client and server may consequently end up with a connection for which
  some security features have been downgraded or disabled, aka a 'Terrapin attack'.

  - CVE-2023-51384: In ssh-agent certain destination constraints can be incompletely applied. When
  destination constraints are specified during addition of PKCS#11-hosted private keys, these
  constraints are only applied to the first key, even if a PKCS#11 token returns multiple keys.

  - CVE-2023-51385: OS command injection might occur if a user name or host name has shell
  metacharacters, and this name is referenced by an expansion token in certain situations. For
  example, an untrusted Git repository can have a submodule with shell metacharacters in a user
  name or host name.|affected=OpenBSD OpenSSH prior to version 9.6.|impact=|solution=Update to version 9.6 or later.

  Note: Client and Server implementations need to run a fixed version to mitigate the Terrapin
  flaw.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 9.6 or later.

  Note: Client and Server implementations need to run a fixed version to mitigate the Terrapin
  flaw.</solution>
        <refs>
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2023-48795" />
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2023-51384" />
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2023-51385" />
