  vulnerabilities in jQuery UI.|insight=jQuery UI is a third-party library used by Drupal. This library
  was previously thought to be end-of-life.

  Late in 2021, jQuery UI announced that they would be continuing development, and released a
  jQuery UI 1.13.0 version.

  It is possible that this vulnerability is exploitable with some Drupal modules. As a precaution,
  this Drupal security release applies the fix for the above cross-site description issue, without
  making any of the other changes to the jQuery version that is included in Drupal.|affected=Drupal version 7.x through 7.85.|impact=|solution=Update to version 7.86 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
