  libgd).|affected=PHP prior to version 5.6.33, 7.0.x prior to 7.0.27, 7.1.x
  prior to 7.1.13 and 7.2.x prior to 7.2.1.|impact=Successfully exploiting these issues allows attacker to execute
  arbitrary script code in the browser of an unsuspecting user in the context of the affected site.
  This may allow the attacker to steal cookie-based authentication credentials and to launch other
  attacks and will also lead to a denial of service and exhausting the server resources.|solution=Update to version 5.6.33, 7.0.27, 7.1.13, 7.2.1 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
