        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N|summary=jQuery is prone to a cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability
  via the load method.|insight=jQuery allows cross-site scripting attacks via the load method.
  The load method fails to recognize and remove '&lt;script&gt;' HTML tags that contain a whitespace
  character, i.e: '&lt;/script &gt;', which results in the enclosed script logic to be executed.|affected=jQuery versions prior to 1.9.0.|impact=|solution=Update to version 1.9.0 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 1.9.0 or later.</solution>
